Kate
text editor
  https://kate-editor.org/

Syntax Highlighting Engine
  https://invent.kde.org/frameworks/syntax-highlighting

How to contribute:
- just send the file to the KWrite-Devel mailing list
  kwrite-devel@kde.org for review
  needed thing: it must be licensed under LGPL for example
- or submit it to the KDE Bugtracking System:
  https://bugs.kde.org/enter_bug.cgi?product=frameworks-syntax-highlighting

-------------------------------------------------------------
Resources location

system's Kate syntax highlighting files are inside file:
  /usr/lib64/libKF5SyntaxHighlighting.so.5.45.0

user's Kate syntax highlighting files are placed into dir:
  ~/.local/share/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/syntax

-------------------------------------------------------------
Useful commands

to validate every XML file by using the command
  validatehl.sh yourSyntax.xml
accompanying files can be taken from:
  https://invent.kde.org/frameworks/syntax-highlighting/data/schema

to get paths where Qt stores a data:
  qtpaths --paths GenericDataLocation

to display the style or others informations associated with each part of text
  ksyntaxhighlighter6 --output-format=ansi --syntax-trace=format test.ijs
